    <item>
      <title>Graph ML for Music Style Modeling</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/projects/graph-ml-music/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/projects/graph-ml-music/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This project explores how graph deep learning can model relationships between songs, artists, harmonic patterns, and stylistic tendencies.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;motivation&#34;&gt;Motivation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I wanted to combine my interests in machine learning and music into a project that is both technically interesting and creatively meaningful.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;methods&#34;&gt;Methods&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;heterogeneous graph construction&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;node and edge feature design&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;graph neural networks for prediction and embedding&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tools&#34;&gt;Tools&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Python, PyTorch Geometric, NetworkX, pandas&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;outcome&#34;&gt;Outcome&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The goal is to better understand stylistic similarity, genre structure, and musical tendencies using graph representations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
